<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>places on nonpunctual</title><link>https://www.nonpunctual.org/places/</link><description>Recent content in places on nonpunctual</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 02 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.nonpunctual.org/places/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Lands End</title><link>https://www.nonpunctual.org/places/lands-end/</link><pubDate>Sat, 02 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.nonpunctual.org/places/lands-end/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;
 Description
 &lt;a class="heading-link" href="#description"&gt;
 &lt;i class="fa-solid fa-link" aria-hidden="true" title="Link to heading"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 &lt;span class="sr-only"&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.nps.gov/goga/planyourvisit/landsend.htm" class="external-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Lands End National Park&lt;/a&gt; is on the northwest edge of San Francisco. It seems like it should be a great area: dramatic views of the wide-open Pacific Ocean &amp;amp; the Golden Gate bridge, giant cargo ships from Asia at anchor, a little bit away from the heart of the city. It&amp;rsquo;s&amp;hellip; ok.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hike was nice, the company was great. Someone dumped a couch in a bushy area off one of the trails. Or, maybe they put it there to, like, sit on. (San Francisco is so weird.)&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Yosemite</title><link>https://www.nonpunctual.org/places/yosemite/</link><pubDate>Sat, 21 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.nonpunctual.org/places/yosemite/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;
